{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_4","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-14-m2-exit-review.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Evolution Note — Milestone 2 Exit Review\n\n## Plan\n\n- path: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- milestone: `Milestone 2 — Board Interaction Quality`\n- bounded target: do one Milestone 2 exit review against `task-plans/board-interaction-quality-task-plan.md` and decide whether the milestone can close\n\n## Completed\n\n- Reviewed Milestone 2 against the current board-interaction task-plan and prior loop slices\n- Confirmed the board now has reliable drag placement, directional resize behavior, explicit `T / S / M / L` semantics, readable compact `Needs Human` cards, and an acceptably isolated drag / resize render path\n- Marked Milestone 2 complete and re-anchored the active plan to Milestone 3 for the next smallest audit slice\n\n## Failed or Deferred\n\n- No code changes were made in this review slice\n- No packaging run was needed because extension behavior did not change\n- Deferred any more board-surface polish because the Milestone 2 exit criteria are already satisfied\n\n## Decisions\n\n- Treat Milestone 2 as complete rather than continuing to invent incremental board tweaks past the published task-plan\n- Move next to a Milestone 3 re-entry audit so the roadmap resumes the next unfinished primary track\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n```text\nContinue the codex-loop from `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md` using `ROADMAP.md` as the anchor. Stay on the current slice only: do one Milestone 3 re-entry audit against `task-plans/insight-and-guidance-task-plan.md`, then update the active plan, append a new evolution note, and sync to `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`.\n```\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
